<body>
	
<header>
	
		
		Which of the following do you think would be good advice to a candidate about to do IELTS Speaking Part 2? Click yes or no against the statements.
		
</header>
	
<section id="body">
	<img class="rightFloat" src="../Media/MM_SP_003.jpg" mode="1" id="1001"  /><br/><ol id="questionList"><br/><li id="1">Talk confidently.  <a id="q1" >Yes</a><tab/><a id="q2" >No</a><br/></li><br/><li id="2">Feel free to correct yourself if you make a mistake. <a id="q3" >Yes</a><tab/><a id="q4" >No</a><br/></li><br/><li id="3">Tell the examiner you are very nervous. <a id="q5" >Yes</a><tab/><a id="q6" >No</a><br/></li><br/><li id="4">Smile and look directly at the examiner. <a id="q7" >Yes</a><tab/><a id="q8" >No</a><br/></li><br/><li id="5">Think of enough material to talk about until the examiner stops you.<a id="q9" >Yes</a><tab/><a id="q10" >No</a><br/></li><br/><li id="6">Show interest in the topic.<a id="q11" >Yes</a><tab/><a id="q12" >No</a><br/></li><br/><li id="7">Learn by heart several short speeches on topics which may come up. <a id="q13" >Yes</a><tab/><a id="q14" >No</a><br/></li><br/><li id="8">Don't speak about something if you know nothing about it. <a id="q15" >Yes</a><tab/><a id="q16" >No</a><br/></li></ol>
</section>
<section id="fb1">
	<p align="left">Confidence is a positive thing and will make what you say more interesting.</p>
</section>
<section id="fb2">
	<p align="left"><font face="verdana" size="13" color="#000000">Correcting yourself shows that you are aware of the mistake and that you know the correct language too. This is positive.</font></p>
</section>
<section id="fb3">
	<p align="left"><font face="verdana" size="13" color="#000000">The examiner expects you to be a bit nervous. There is no need to say it.</font></p>
</section>
<section id="fb4">
	<p align="left"><font face="verdana" size="13" color="#000000">This is a friendly thing to do and helps establish good communication.</font></p>
</section>
<section id="fb5">
	<p align="left"><font face="verdana" size="13" color="#000000">In Part 2 it is good to talk until the examiner stops you.</font></p>
</section>
<section id="fb6">
	<p align="left"><font face="verdana" size="13" color="#000000">If you show interest, then what you say will be more interesting to the examiner.</font></p>
</section>
<section id="fb7">
	<p align="left"><font face="verdana" size="13" color="#000000">Learning by heart will not help you in this exam. It may cause you to lose marks.</font></p>
</section>
<section id="fb8">
	<p align="left"><font face="verdana" size="13" color="#000000">You are not expected to know everything, but you should express an opinion or some thoughts on everything you are asked.</font></p>
</section>
